label: هذا کتاب نجوم بطلمىوس ; رساله معىنيه در علم هيئت.
[Hāz̲ā Kitāb-i Nujūm-i Baṭlamyūs] ; Risālah-i Muʻīnīyah dar ʻilm-i hayʾat.
description: Title of first text from fol. 1a, by a later hand; title of second text from fol. 54a.
On front cover: Label reading "284" in Arabic script.
Ms. erroneously foliated beginning on first flyleaf. Record follows erroneous foliation.

Physical description: 15-16 lines per page; written in casual nastaʻliq by two different hands in black on glazed, laid Arabic paper. Rubrication and catchwords. Some damp staining; edges somewhat ragged.
Origin: First text completed Ramaḍān 935 H [May-June 1529] by Muḥammad Ḥusayn al-Ḥasanī (fol. 53a). Second text completed on Wednesday, 7 Rabīʻ II 681 H [15 July 1282] (fol. 130a).

metadata.label: Author
value: Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274

metadata.label: Abstract
value: Two texts on astrology and astronomy by Naṣīr al-Dīn al-Ṭūsī.

metadata.label: Contents
value: 1. fol. 3a-53a: [Sharḥ-i S̲amarah-i Baṭlamyūs]. Persian translation of and commentary on an Arabic version of Ptolemy's Centiloquium, a collection of a hundred aphorisms on astrology. With original Arabic text; missing first page.

2. fol. 54a-130a: Risālah-i Muʻīnīyah dar ʻilm-i hayʾat. Manual of astronomy dedicated to Muʻīn al-Dīn Abū al-Shams, son of the author's patron Nāṣir al-Dīn ʻAbd al-Raḥīm ibn Abī Manṣūr (governor of Quhistan). Missing first page; with numerous diagrams.

metadata.label: Extent
value: 128 leaves : paper, ill. ; 191 x 119 (147 x 77-85) bound to 191 x 125 mm.
